-- Bank of America Appeals $590 Million Ruling in Lehman Case, Filings Show
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2010-12-16T14:18:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-16/bank-of-america-to-appeal-590-million-ruling-in-lehman-case-filings-show.html
Bank of America Corp., ordered by a
bankruptcy judge to pay  Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.  $590
million after taking its deposits, appealed the ruling and said
it would post a $660 million bond if the judge would hold off on
enforcing his order pending result of the appeal, according to
filings yesterday in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Manhattan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Linda Sandler  in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David E. Rovella at   drovella@bloomberg.net . 